<br>
Pick Lock is a skill only given to two classes, but outside of LDoN, only benificial to one of these classes, Rogue.  While I will be the first to agree that the rogues enjoy monopolization of all theivery skills (Pick Lock, Pick Pocket, SoS Sneak / Hide, and Backstabbing) as a form of class definition, permiting Pick Lock in particular to be a utility of a single class hinders the enjoyment of former content by the greater majority of players; and especially bards.  As an example, Breath of Harmony and Guise of the Hunter are two items in out-dated content designed to be enjoyed by Bards which are sealed in camps behind doors only accessable to Rogue-Level Pick Lock skill.  For a Bard of maximum level, maximum alternate advancement points, maximum Bard Pick Lock skill, and the highest skill-modification items (mechanized lockpicks and gloves of the brood), the bard would still require a Rogue of a mere level 50 to gain access to Lower Undead Sebilis, or 60 to gain access to the Shissar Assassin in the Temple of Ssrashzea, which I personally feel is absurd.  Why taunt our class with the pick lock skill for 5 years, small skill upgrades as in ldon, advanced trap negotiation alternate advancement skill, as well as the ability to use the highest Pick Lock mod items, while still refusing us the ability to open doors in long outdated content?<br>
<br>
To address the issue of class definition I would like to use Lost Dungeons of Norrath as refference.  In this expansion bard pick lock skill was raised to 125 to allow bards the option of accessing chests and containers in adventures where a rogue was not present.  This was a fantastic step to making our long-forgotten skill more valuable and did not cause class unbalance, did not make rogues useless, and did not cause a large uproar from the rogue community for infrengements on rogue class defining skills.  Why can this example not be expanded to include past expansional content? <br>
<br>
As a bard, I don't expect to be able to take the rogues job of opening current and future progressive content such as the Ikkinz raid which requires an item to be pick-pocketed to proceede, I simply desire the ability to enter content that is trivial to me.<br>
<br>
Proposed Solution:  Alternate Advancement Skill, Five Ranks, 5 / 5 / 5 / 5 / 5, Increase Max Pick Lock skill by 15 per rank.<br>
<br>
Alternative Solution: Song Self only: Double current pick lock skill for all pick lock checks while song is active.<br>
<br>
These are just two ideas on how to make the bard pick lock skill a universally viable skill, as well as increasing the enjoyment of out-dated content by making it accessable to more players.<br>
<br>
